                                <pubPlace>М.–Л.</pubPlace>: <publisher>Наука</publisher>,
                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><xi:include href="../encodingdesc.xml" parse="xml"/></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_fynk" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>fynk</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>finkæ</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>пена</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>foam</q></abv:tr></sense><re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>fynk kænyn</orth></form></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>fynk kalyn</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>пениться</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>to foam</q></abv:tr></sense></re></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>komy fynk</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>пена изо рта</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>foam at the mouth</q></abv:tr></sense></re><abv:exampleGrp><abv:example><quote>...æmæ jæ komy fynk kaly æmæ jæ dændægtæj kʼæs-kʼæs kæny</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>... и он извергает пену и скрежещет зубами своими</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>...and he foameth, and gnasheth with his teeth</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Марк"/><biblScope>%i9%i 18</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>balastoncæ æ falʒæstæ æ gar togi finkitæj</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>вокруг него разлилась пена его теплой крови</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>the foam of his warm blood spilled around him</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Bes."/><biblScope>97</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>dælfinkæj cʼæx ku ferttevuj felawæn...</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>когда из-под пены блеснет голубая волна...</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>when a blue wave flashes from under the foam...</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>41</biblScope></bibl></abv:example></abv:exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>*faina-ka-</w></mentioned>. Заключает общеиндоевропейский корень, оформленный в индоиранском и славяно-балтийском элементом %in%i, а в германском и латинском элементом %im%i: <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>phena-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/> <w>пѣна</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <w>пена, пенка</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="prg"><lang/> <w>spaoyno</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/> <w>spáine</w> <gloss><q>пена</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="goh"><lang/> <w>feim</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ang"><lang/> <w>fám</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/> <w>spūma</w> <gloss><q>пена</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w>pūmex</w> <gloss><q>пемза</q></gloss></mentioned>; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>spāma-</w> <gloss><q>слизь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>pynʼkh</w> <gloss><q>пена</q></gloss></mentioned>. Дифтонг %iai%i дает обычно %iе%i в дигорском, %ii%i в иронском. Но перед %in%i он ослабляется соответственно в %ii%i и %iу%i; ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wynyn"/> | %iwinun%i ‘видеть’ из %i*vain-%i, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_synæg"/> | %isinæg%i из %i*sainaka-%i.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 56</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>18, 27, 34</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><author>Meillet</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_BSL"/><biblScope>XXXI 51</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>19, 352</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>*faina-ka-</w></mentioned>. It contains a common Indo-European root, formed with an element %in%i in Indo-Iranian and Slavic-Baltic, and with an element %im%i in Germanic and Latin: <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>phena-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/> <w>пѣна</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <w>пена, пенка</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="prg"><lang/> <w>spaoyno</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/> <w>spáine</w> <gloss><q>foam</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="goh"><lang/> <w>feim</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ang"><lang/> <w>fám</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/> <w>spūma</w> <gloss><q>foam</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w>pūmex</w> <gloss><q>pumice stone</q></gloss></mentioned>; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>spāma-</w> <gloss><q>slime</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>pynʼkh</w> <gloss><q>foam</q></gloss></mentioned>. A diphthong %iai%i usually gives %iе%i in Digor and %ii%i in Iron. However, before %in%i it weakens to%ii%i and %iу%i, correspondingly; compare with <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wynyn"/> | %iwinun%i ‘see’ from %i*vain-%i, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_synæg"/> | %isinæg%i from %i*sainaka-%i.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 56</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>18, 27, 34</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><author>Meillet</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_BSL"/><biblScope>XXXI 51</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>19, 352</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>